				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/logansorenssen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334609); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=334609&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205776" alt="logansorenssen" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=334609)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/logansorenssen" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(334609); return false;" >logansorenssen</a></span> <span class="odate time_1254121276 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">28 Sep 2009 07:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-595292">
									

<p>I'm not contesting the removal - it can definitely be argued the material was irrelevant or didn't add enough - but Gold Alfa Vacuum wasn't wrong NATO phonetic for "GAV". It was intended to be a security codeword using the pattern 'color, NATO phonetic letter, nonsense placeholder word'. GAV was just a shortened version of the full codeword, which could, for added confusion, be expanded to Golf Alpha (or Alfa, that's a different dispute) Victor.</p>

							</div>

								
					
