    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-696239">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-696239">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,696239)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-696239">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/leicontis" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(393373); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=393373&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610205776" alt="Leicontis" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=393373)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/leicontis" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(393373); return false;" >Leicontis</a></span> <span class="odate time_1265813000 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Feb 2010 14:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-696239">
									

<p>It's mysterious, to the point where one doesn't know if it even exists (at least in this world/universe). It seems to mass-produce incredibly useful (and Safe-class) SCPs, which appeals to me because I'm the type that tries to look for uses for SCPs. You never know if you've got all of a given object, or if there are more floating around somewhere, or if more will be produced and appear later. You're dealing with an unknown party that apparently possesses extremely advanced technology, and you've got no idea who or where they are, nor what their agenda is.</p>
<p>Ideally, I'd like to see no new information appear on The Factory - the very fact that <em>none</em> of the major groups (the Foundation, MC&amp;D, CBG, IRG, CI) seem to know anything about it adds greatly to the mystique.</p>

							</div>

								
					
